  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.org/heritagedata/schemes/365/concepts/123430">
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Rectangular slabs of concrete with a sloping top usually with sides of 5 feet by 3 feet and 3 feet high which when placed in rows were intended to form a substantial barrier to enemy armoured divisions in the event of invasion.</skos:scopeNote>
